  "prompt": "My viber on PC doesnt connect to internet. whats the problem? It shows me the messages that other send me but I cant reply through my pc.",
  "response": "If your Viber on PC is showing messages but not allowing you to send replies, it may be experiencing connectivity issues or other technical difficulties. Here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot the problem:\n\n1. **Check Internet Connection**: Ensure that your PC has a stable internet connection. You can test this by opening a web browser and visiting any website.\n\n2. **Restart Viber**: Close Viber completely and then reopen it. This can help refresh the connection.\n\n3. **Update Viber**: Make sure you are using the latest version of Viber. Check for updates and install any if available.\n\n4. **Reboot Your Computer**: Sometimes, simply rebooting your PC can resolve connectivity issues.\n\n5. **Firewall/Antivirus Settings**: Check if your firewall or antivirus software is blocking Viber. You may need to allow Viber through your firewall settings.\n\n6. **Network Settings**:\n   - Make sure you're not using a VPN or proxy that might be interfering with Viber's connectivity.\n   - Try switching between Wi-Fi and Ethernet, or reconnect your network.\n\n7. **Unlink and Relink**: You can try unlinking your Viber account from your PC and then relinking it:\n   - Open Viber on your phone, go to \"More\" > \"Settings\" > \"Account\" > \"Linked Devices\".\n   - Unlink your PC, then run Viber on your PC and scan the QR code using your phone to link it again.\n\n8. **Reinstall Viber**: As a last resort, uninstall Viber from your PC and then download and install the latest version again.\n\nIf none of these steps work, it may also be helpful to check Viber's official support pages or community forums for any ongoing issues or additional troubleshooting steps.",
